    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: BENDIX 2150 - DISASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The following instructions are presented here for reference. Removal and disassembly of the compressor
                is not recommended unless the appropriate service parts and/or kits are on hand.
            </para>
            <para>Remove road dirt and grease from the exterior of the compressor with a cleaning solvent. Before the
                compressor is disassembled, the following items should be marked to show their relationship when the
                compressor is assembled (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0400411">Figure 11</hotlnk>). Mark the rear end cover in relation to the crankcase.
                Mark the cylinder head in relation to the crankcase. Mark the base plate or base adapter in relation to
                the crankcase.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0400411" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400411" filename="../figg04/G0400411.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Exploded View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>CYLINDER HEAD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
